@le_sserafim fans, rejoice: “Celebration” is here. The K-pop girl group just dropped their new song and music video ahead of their upcoming album ‘Pureflow pt.1.,’ which comes out May 22. The single is exactly as the name suggests, a pounding track that invites listeners into the party set to a music video complete with the full group devouring their choreography.
“‘Celebration’ is kind of about that moment when you look back and realize, ‘I got through it,’” the group tells ELLE. “It’s not about something huge or perfect—it’s more about appreciating yourself for still being here after everything.”
#Le_Sserafim took us exclusively behind the scenes of the shoot for “Celebration”—now at the link in bio.

@kith teams up with NYC-based wagwear for its first-ever pet collection, blending style and utility across dog apparel, walking gear, and home essentials. Highlights include the Nylon Rainbreaker and reflective Padded Harness (XS–XL), plus a durable Rope Leash with grip-friendly design. wagwear’s cult-favorite WagWellies Mojave boots return in Black and Yellow, built to protect paws from hot pavement while staying breathable and secure.⁠
⁠
For smaller breeds, the monogrammed Zipper Tote Carrier offers water-resistant lining and built-in safety features. The lineup rounds out with chew-friendly non-toxic bones and sleek stainless steel bowls. The collection drops April 27 at 11 AM via Kith’s Monday Program, available in-store, online, and on the app across New York, London, Paris, and Tokyo.

@JacobAndCo. unveils the Godfather II, a $440,000 musical timepiece that brings cinema to the wrist.
Drawing inspiration from one of film’s most iconic sagas, the watch integrates two legendary compositions — The Godfather’s Waltz and The Godfather Love Theme — played through an intricate, built-in music box.
Encased in a sculpted Art Deco-inspired design, the piece combines horological artistry with cinematic storytelling. A flying tourbillon, dual power reserves, and a newly engineered movement elevate both its technical and aesthetic appeal, while the dial features a finely detailed portrait of Don Corleone alongside subtle references to the film’s legacy.
Limited to just 74 pieces, in tribute to the 1974 release of The Godfather Part II, the timepiece stands as a rare collector’s creation, where music, craftsmanship, and heritage converge.
